RACE.RACE_TEXT: Old Timers Classic S. CENTURY MILE RACE 1 300 Y Dirt CR: 79. Stakes Purse 21960. A STAKE FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD QUARTER HORSES. A payment of $200.00 is required at time of entry. Preference guides can be found in the AQHRA Stakes Book. Weight: Three-Year-Olds 124 lbs. Older: 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JESSAPRIMADONNA drifted in under right-handed encouragement mid-stretch while closing steadily and was up in time. FLIGHT CLUB lead the way early, and was caught late. DOUBLE CRUISE close throughout. BRINGONTHERUSH raced evenly throughout. SHE WEARS THE PANTZ rallied late. SCARLETTS CARTEL lacked running room between rivals late. WAVE BURNER broke outward, and offered a late bid. TIMBERS EXPRESS left at the gate and did not receive a fair start. STEWARDS INQUIRY- The Stewards conducted an inquiry into the start of the race involving TIMBERS EXPRESS. After reviewing the Stewards concluded that TIMBERS EXPRESS did not receive a fair start. All monies wagered on TIMBERS EXPRES were refunded.

ENTRY.NAME: Jessaprimadonna
ENTRY.COMMENT: drifted in, closed steadily, up in time

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 88. Starter Allowance Purse 15500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 (AB $10,000) OR LESS IN THEIR LAST THREE STARTS AND HAVE NOT WON A STARTER SINCE STARTING FOR CLAIMING PRICE OF $8,000 (AB $10,000) OR LESS. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 127 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AWHITESPORTSCOAT stalked inside early, shifted out leaving the final turn, dueled late stretch outside of SCHOCHOH, and was up with time. SCHOCHOH showed the way leaving the backstretch, was under pressure at the head of the stretch, and was out finished. EL NOBLE chased three wide leaving the backstretch, angled inside mid-stretch, and was outkicked. BORKAN brushed leaving then trailed the field early, and closed well late. FAST EH brushed leaving, sat just off the pace in the two path, was roused at the head of the lane, and failed to threaten. YORKTOWN jostled away, sat off the pace, and lacked a bid.

ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked inside, dueled, up with time

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MI REYNA vied outside early, settled in striking position through the turn, was given a cue then overtook the leader quickly, and won going away. DEFINITE PLEASURE vied for the early lead, showed the way through the turn, was overtaken approaching the stretch, and finished evenly. ADDYDIDIT saved ground inside, and rallied late for the show. FLORIST raced four wide into the opening turn, and offered a belated bid. SHE LOVES WINNIN jostled away, was reserved off the pace, shifted outside, and tired in the stretch. IT'S ALEXUS offered little. TAKE CHARGE GWEN trailed throughout.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 4 5F Dirt CR: 55. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 127 lbs. Claiming Price $6,000. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUBLIME EUPHORIA stumbled leaving then was brushed, emerged the leader leaving the backstretch, remained unchallenged through the stretch and held under a late bid by DYLAN'S SAVE. DYLAN'S SAVE rated off the pacesetter, raced five wide through the lane, closed determinedly and missed. STUBBORN LOVE lacked a clear path when leaving the gate, hustled quickly inside, roused three wide at the head of the lane, rallied inside of DYLAN'S SAVE but was outkicked. SHES MY DESTINY chased outside and improved late. SUNDROP sandwiched leaving, took closer order into the final turn, shifted out to the two path at the head of the stretch, and offered a mild bid. INDIAN GIRL broke outward into SUNDROP, and was roused to no avail. LANA'S PRETTY GIRL broke inward then was bumped, and was outrun.

ENTRY.COMMENT: lacked clear path, hustled inside, outkicked

FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $12,000 WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR ALBERTA BREDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 127 lbs. Non-winners Of A Ra ce In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,000. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOOTIFUL ROSE hurried inside to secure the lead, two back challenge from NIGHT FLYER at the head of the stretch, and drove clear under a strong hand ride. NIGHT FLYER chased BOOTIFUL ROSE through the final turn, moved up menacingly but was unable to stall the winner and just held on for second. QUEEN RHONDA saved ground along the rail, launched an all-out bid, and missed out on place honors. MOHAYMEN DAY was allowed to settle off the pace, and lodged a mild bid. THRILL OF THE NITE sat in striking range outside, swung four to five wide at the quarter pole, and faded in the stretch. SOFIA D 'AMORE sat in range while four wide, and lacked a response when called upon. LILBITSPICY settled near the back of the field, and lacked a solid bid. FAMOUS LAST WORDS trailed throughout.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 6 5F Dirt CR: 67. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 127 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Lesser Claiming Races Not Considered In Eligibility). Alberta Bred Cl aiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BABS DELIGHT sat in striking position along the rail, responded to handling into the stretch, gained the lead with a sixteenth remaining and held under a drive. EYESPYMYLITTLEEYE quickly went to the front, lacked the response needed when challenged by BABS DELIGHT and held firm for second. BIG CYN broke outward bumping into MY EXPRESSION, drifted outward in the backstretch, chased four wide, moved up alongside EYESPYMYLITTLEEYE but was unable to muster the rally needed to improve the position late. TALA broke outward into ENTITLED STAR, raced four to five wide, and closed belatedly. OUT FRONT stalked the pace, and lacked a closing response. MY EXPRESSION brushed leaving, and offered a mild bid. DAZZLING CHIC offered little. ENTITLED STAR brushed leaving, and was never involved. KISSABLE U stumbled badly losing the rider from the gate, did not finish, and walked off. STEWARDS INQUIRY- The Stewards conducted an inquiry into the start of the race involving KISSABLE U but made no change, as KISSABLE U stumbled leaving the gate.

ENTRY.NAME: Big Cyn
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke outward, drifted out, chased 4w, needed more

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 7 5F Dirt CR: 78. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 127 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,000. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AMUSING WAY broke sharply to lead the way, remained uncovered into the lane, and opened up on the field. AMEER chased along the rail, and got by late. CHARMING VINTAGE unhurried early, dueled inside of ICE BOX INDY, and was caught late settling for show. ICE BOX INDY brushed JAKE THE RAKE leaving, fanned three wide into the opening turn, dueled outside of CHARMING VINTAGE, and gave way late stretch. JAKE THE RAKE brushed leaving, fanned four wide, and lacked a kick. AGENT C trailed early and passed tiring. KEEP YOUR COOL broke outward, fanned five wide in the opening turn, and came up empty in the drive under the encouragement. FIRST BASE in range early and tired.

ENTRY.OWNER: Salt River Holdings Inc and Viking Stables

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 8 5F Dirt CR: 86. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 19500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $17,500. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 127 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $17,500. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $22,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BON PRIX quickly went to the front, kept to task through the stretch, and held safely. GLAVA broke outward into COUNTRIFIED, sat in striking range early, was roused entering the stretch, closed steadily late, and held. SMARTY RIVER PANTS saved inside, shifted out at the head of the lane, and closed well missing out late. DRINKING AGAIN showed early speed inside, dropped back, and improved late. ABOVE AND BEYOND jostled leaving, took closer order nearing the quarter pole, and rallied late. COUNTRIFIED bumped leaving, and offered a mild bid late. FLASHFORDANI brushed leaving, sat mid pack in the three path, and lacked a kick. HARD TO COME HOME broke inward leaving, chased the pace through the turn, and yielded along the rail. ESCROW STYLE was not a factor. IMPERIAL BIRD left at the gate and did not receive a fair start. STEWARDS INQUIRY- The Board of Stewards conducted an inquiry into the start of the race involving IMPERIAL BIRD. After review, IMPERIAL BIRD was deemed to have had an unfair start. All monies wagered on IMPERIAL BIRD were refunded.
